cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method to improve the performance of CNNs in general vision tasks by leveraging styles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper introduces a new architectural unit for CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves recalibrating feature maps, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper conducts experiments on image recognition, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM).
